I"‹<p>JobAdder is a global recruitment platform built for staffing agency and in-house corporate recruiters. Used by over 10,000 people every day, we empower recruiters all over the world to recruit smarter and simpler.</p>

<h1 id="navigation-redesign">Navigation Redesign</h1>

<h2 id="problem">Problem</h2>

<p>The previous navigation was a full width, persistent and took up 1/4 of the screen at all times. Users had always made comments and complaints about not being able to use the full height of the screen to view jobs, job ads and candidates.</p>

<h2 id="previous-design">Previous design</h2>

<div class="w-full px-2 py-1">
  <img data-action="zoom" src="/image/work/jobadder/nav-old.png" />
</div>

<h2 id="new-design">New design</h2>

<div class="w-full px-2 py-1">
  <img data-action="zoom" src="/image/work/jobadder/nav-new.png" />
</div>

<h2 id="my-role">My role</h2>

<p>I worked with the Product Manager, <a href="https://twitter.com/dysontom" target="\_blank">Tom Dyson</a>, and JobAdder CEO, <a href="https://twitter.com/BrettIredale" target="\_blank">Brett Iredale</a>, to empathise with the users to understand and define the problem.</p>

<p>Starting with mapping the information architecture of the JobAdder suite of products with the aim to iterate and streamline the complex world of JobAdder.</p>

<p>I researched equally complex SaaS products to explore how others solved the same problem. Using them as inspiration to help evolve potential options.</p>

<p>I created wireframe upon wireframe with no fear of failure, just aiming to throw as many ideas at the wall to see what sticks.</p>

