<p>Working closely with the developer, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexandre-periphanos" target="\_blank">Alex Periphanos</a>, the navigation was implemented so we were able to test it with out users.</p>

<h2 id="learnings-and-iteration">Learnings and iteration</h2>

<p>The average JobAdder user isn‚Äôt overly tech savvy so I chose to limit breaking mental modals where possible. Instead of restructuring the information architecture, I left that to a future version.</p>

<p>Another important choice was to default to the navigation being expanded. Initially having the labels visible will allow the users to easily navigate and when comfortable, collapse the nav to utilize more of the screen.</p>

<h2 id="results">Results</h2>

<p>The navigation launched mid-December, after a small group of users got access to it with positive feedback. Once globally live, the feedback too was overwhelmingly positive.</p>

